                @* <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.NewsDetail.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> *@
                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.NewsSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>
                <p><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="TWBrandDetails" asp-route-brandId="1">Royal Enfield</a> has expanded its 350cc lineup with the introduction of the Goan Classic 350, a bold bobber-style motorcycle, set to launch at Motoverse 2024 in Goa. This model takes inspiration from the popular Classic 350 while embracing a unique retro-modern design.</p>
                <p>At its core, the Goan Classic 350 houses the reliable 349cc single-cylinder, air-cooled engine from the J-Series platform, delivering 20 bhp and 27 Nm of torque. Paired with a 5-speed gearbox, the engine ensures the refined performance Royal Enfield riders expect.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldrevelstheallnewgoanclassic350bobber/2.webp" alt="Royal Enfield Reveals the All New Goan Classic 350 Bobber - 1" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>What sets this bike apart is its aesthetic and ergonomic transformation. The Goan Classic 350 features a shortened subframe, a solo saddle with the option for a pillion, and a striking exposed rear fender. Its tall ape handlebars and forward-set footpegs promise a relaxed, cruiser-like riding stance, perfect for long scenic journeys. Additionally, white-walled tyres and vibrant color schemes add to its retro charm.</p>               
                <p>For practicality, it includes advanced safety features like dual-channel ABS and disc brakes on both ends. The suspension setup comprises telescopic forks upfront and twin shock absorbers at the rear, ensuring comfort on varied terrains.</p>
                <p>Expected to be priced at approximately ₹2 lakh (ex-showroom), this new addition positions itself slightly above the Classic 350. Competing against models like the Jawa Perak, it caters to riders who prioritize both style and substance.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldrevelstheallnewgoanclassic350bobber/3.webp" alt="Royal Enfield Reveals the All New Goan Classic 350 Bobber - 2" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Specifications:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Engine:</span> 349cc single-cylinder, air-cooled</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Power/Torque:</span> 20 bhp, 27 Nm</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Transmission:</span> 5-speed gearbox</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Braking System:</span> Dual disc with ABS</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Suspension:</span> Telescopic front forks, twin rear shock absorbers</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Price:</span> Approx. ₹2 lakh (ex-showroom)</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
